<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-3903] javadocs very very ugly if you generate with java7</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-3903</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;Java7 changes its javadocs to look much nicer, but this involves different CSS styles.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Lucene overrides the CSS with stylesheet+prettify.css which is a combination of java5/6 stylesheet + google prettify:&lt;br/&gt;
but there are problems because java7 has totally different styles.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So if you generate javadocs with java7, its like you have no stylesheet at all.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A solution might be to make stylesheet7+prettify.css and conditionalize a property in ant based on java version.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
